00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:08,790
<i>O mothers, let's go down</i>

281
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:12,190
<i>Come on down, don't you wanna go down ?</i>

282
00:18:12,390 --> 00:18:15,990
<i>Come on, mothers, let's go down...</i>

283
00:18:16,190 --> 00:18:19,190
Well, I guess hard times flush the chumps.

284
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:21,390
Everybody's lookin' for answers.

285
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:26,790
Where the hell's he going ?

286
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:30,790
The Father, the Son and the Holy Ghost.

287
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:34,790
<i>Good Lord, show me the way</i>

288
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:39,290
<i>O sinners, let's go down...</i>

289
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:41,790
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

290
00:18:41,990 --> 00:18:43,890
Delmar's been saved.

291
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,990
Well, that's it, boys. I been redeemed.

292
00:18:47,190 --> 00:18:51,290
The preacher done washed away
all my sins and transgressions.

293
00:18:51,490 --> 00:18:54,190
It's the straight and narrow from here on out.

294
00:18:54,490 --> 00:18:56,890
And heaven everlasting's my reward.

295
00:18:57,090 --> 00:19:00,190
Delmar, what are you on about?
We got bigger fish to fry.

296
00:19:00,390 --> 00:19:03,290
The preacher said all my sins is washed away,

297
00:19:03,490 --> 00:19:06,390
including that Piggly Wiggly
I knocked over in Yazoo.

298
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:08,590
I thought you said you was innocent of that.

299
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:10,990
Well, I was lyin'.

300
00:19:11,190 --> 00:19:14,790
And the preacher said that
that sin's been washed away, too.

301
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:18,190
Neither God nor man's got nothin' on me now.

302
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:23,190
Come on in, boys. The water is fine.

303
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:31,590
Come on boy, there, boy. Good doggy.

304
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:37,690
All right, boys, we got the scent.
He don't care if we bring'em back dead does he?

305
00:19:40,190 --> 00:19:43,790
- The preacher said it absolved us.
- For Him, not for the law.

306
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:46,720
Surprised at you Pete,
I gave you credit for more brains than Delmar.

307
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:50,690
- But they was witnesses seen us redeemed.
- That's not the issue, Delmar.

308
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:54,090
Even if it did put you square with the Lord, the
state of Mississippi's a little more hard-nosed.

309
00:19:54,290 --> 00:19:57,590
You shoulda joined us Everett,
it couldn'a hurt none.

310
00:19:57,790 --> 00:20:01,090
Hell, it woulda washed away
the stink of that pomade.

311
00:20:01,390 --> 00:20:04,790
Join you two ignorant fools in a rediculous
superstition thank you, anyway...

312
00:20:05,090 --> 00:20:10,190
and I like the smell of my hair treatment,
the pleasin' odour's half the point.

313
00:20:10,390 --> 00:20:12,290
Baptism!

314
00:20:12,490 --> 00:20:14,690
You two are just dumber than a bag of hammers.

315
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:16,790
Well, I guess you're my cross to bear.

316
00:20:16,990 --> 00:20:21,690
Pull over, Everett. Let's give
that coloured boy a lift.

317
00:20:27,390 --> 00:20:29,690
You folks going past Tishomingo?

318
00:20:29,890 --> 00:20:32,690
Sure, hop in.

319
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:41,590
How you doin' son, name's Everett.

320
00:20:41,890 --> 00:20:45,090
These two soggy sons of bitches
are Pete and Delmar.

321
00:20:45,390 --> 00:20:48,990
Keep your fingers away from Pete's mouth, 
he ain't had nothin' to eat for 13 years,

322
00:20:49,190 --> 00:20:51,390
'cept prison food, gopher and a little greasy horse.

323
00:20:51,690 --> 00:20:55,390
Thanks for the lift, sir.
My name's Tommy, Tommy Johnson.

324
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:57,490
How you doin', Tommy?

325
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:00,590
Say, I haven't seen a house out here for miles.

326
00:21:00,890 --> 00:21:03,290
What are you doin' out in the middle of nowhere?

327
00:21:03,490 --> 00:21:06,090
I had to be at that there crossroads last midnight.

328
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:08,190
Sell my soul to the devil.

329
00:21:08,390 --> 00:21:10,790
Ain't it a small world, spiritually speakin'?

330
00:21:10,990 --> 00:21:14,990
Pete and Delmar just been baptised and saved.
I'm guess I'm the only one that remains unaffiliated.

331
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:17,290
It's no laughin' matter.

332
00:21:17,590 --> 00:21:19,290
What'd the devil give you for your soul Tommy?

333
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:22,790
Well, he taught me to play this here guitar real good.

334
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:27,090
Oh, son, for that you traded your everlasting soul?

335
00:21:27,390 --> 00:21:28,790
Well, I wasn't usin' it.

336
00:21:28,990 --> 00:21:32,990
I've always wondered, what's the devil look like?

337
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:36,590
Well, 'course there are all manner
of lesser imps and demons Pete

338
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:40,290
but the great Satan hisself is red and scaly
with a bifurcated tail,

339
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:43,890
- and he carries a hayfork.
- Oh, no. no, sir.

340
00:21:44,090 --> 00:21:47,390
He's white... as white as you folks.

341
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:50,390
With empty eyes and a big, hollow voice.

342
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:54,190
He loved to travel 'round
with a mean old hound, that's right.

343
00:21:54,390 --> 00:21:56,290
He told you to go to Tishomingo?

344
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:59,190
Well, no sir... why, that was my idea.

345
00:21:59,490 --> 00:22:01,190
I heard there's a man down there,

346
00:22:01,490 --> 00:22:03,690
he pays folks money to sing into his can.

347
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:07,690
They say he pays extra if'n you play real good.

348
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:09,690
Tishomingo, huh?

349
00:22:09,890 --> 00:22:11,390
How much he pay?

350
00:22:27,190 --> 00:22:31,690
All right boys follow my lead.

351
00:22:35,590 --> 00:22:37,890
Hello?

352
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:42,590
- Who's the honcho here?
- I am, who are you?

353
00:22:42,790 --> 00:22:47,090
Well, sir, I'm Jordan Rivers,
and these here are the Soggy Bottom Boys,

354
00:22:47,290 --> 00:22:49,190
out of Cottonillia, Mississippi.

355
00:22:49,390 --> 00:22:51,690
Songs of salvation to salve the soul.

356
00:22:51,990 --> 00:22:55,590
Uh, we hear that you pay good money
to sing into a can.

357
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:58,990
Well, that all depends. You boys do Negra songs?

358
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:03,890
Um... Well, uh, sir, we are Negroes.

359
00:23:04,090 --> 00:23:07,990
All except for our accomp... accomp...
the fella that plays the guitar.

360
00:23:08,190 --> 00:23:10,290
Yeah, well, I don't record Negra songs.

361
00:23:10,590 --> 00:23:13,790
No, I'm lookin' for some old-timey material.

362
00:23:14,090 --> 00:23:16,050
Seem people can't get enough of it.

363
00:23:16,190 --> 00:23:19,490
since we started broadcasting it
on the Pappy O'Daniel Flour Hour,

364
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:21,890
so thank you for stopping by, but...

365
00:23:22,190 --> 00:23:26,790
Sir, the Soggy Bottom Boys have been
steeped in old-timey material.

366
00:23:26,990 --> 00:23:29,590
Heck, we're silly with it, ain't we boys.
- That's right.

367
00:23:29,890 --> 00:23:31,790
That's right, we ain't really Negroes.

368
00:23:32,090 --> 00:23:34,090
All except for our accompanist.

369
00:23:36,590 --> 00:23:40,690
<i>I am a man</i>

370
