00:24:47,990 --> 00:24:50,290
<i>My face you never</i>

391
00:24:50,590 --> 00:24:51,790
<i>Will see no more</i>

392
00:24:54,190 --> 00:24:58,790
<i>But there is one promise</i>

393
00:24:59,090 --> 00:25:00,990
<i>That is given</i>

394
00:25:01,190 --> 00:25:03,690
<i>I'll meet you on</i>

395
00:25:03,990 --> 00:25:06,390
<i>God's golden shore</i>

396
00:25:06,690 --> 00:25:09,190
<i>He'll meet you on</i>

397
00:25:09,390 --> 00:25:14,190
<i>God's golden shore</i>

398
00:25:15,490 --> 00:25:18,890
Whoo! Hot damn, son!
I do believe you did sell your soul to the devil!

399
00:25:20,590 --> 00:25:24,290
Boy, that was some mighty fine
a-pickin' and a-singin'.

400
00:25:24,490 --> 00:25:25,790
I'll tell you what.

401
00:25:25,990 --> 00:25:28,190
Ahem. You come on in here, you...

402
00:25:28,390 --> 00:25:32,690
you sign these papers here,
I'm gonna give you $10 apiece.

403
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:38,890
Uh, OK, sir, but Mert and...
Aloysious'll have to just sign x's.

404
00:25:39,190 --> 00:25:42,990
Only four of us can write.
That'd be fine.

405
00:25:45,790 --> 00:25:48,990
Hey, mister, I don't mean
to tell tales out of school,

406
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:52,890
but there's a fella in there'll pay
you $10 if you sing into his can.

407
00:25:53,190 --> 00:25:56,090
I'm not here to make a record, you dumb cracker.

408
00:25:56,290 --> 00:25:58,090
They broadcast me out on the radio.

409
00:25:58,290 --> 00:26:01,090
That's Governor Menelaus "Pass-the-biscuits Pappy" O'Daniel.

410
00:26:01,390 --> 00:26:05,290
He'd sure appreciate it if you ate his
farina and voted him a second term.

411
00:26:05,590 --> 00:26:08,090
- Finest Governor we ever had in Mississippi.
- In any state.

412
00:26:08,390 --> 00:26:10,570
Oh Lord yes, every parish or precinct...
He was making a bigger point...

413
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:13,585
Hey,ain't you gonna press the flesh, Pappy?
Do a little politickin'?

414
00:26:13,590 --> 00:26:16,690
I'll press your flesh, you dim-witted son'bitch.

415
00:26:16,890 --> 00:26:20,590
Don't you tell your Pappy how to court the
elecorate, we ain't one-at-a-timin' it here

416
00:26:20,890 --> 00:26:22,490
we're mass communicatin'!

417
00:26:22,690 --> 00:26:25,190
Oh, yes, that's a powerful new force.

418
00:26:25,390 --> 00:26:26,790
Shake a leg, Junior.

419
00:26:26,990 --> 00:26:29,290
Thank God your mammy died givin' birth,

420
00:26:29,490 --> 00:26:30,990
she'd a seen ya, she'd a died of shame.

421
00:26:31,190 --> 00:26:33,090
Well, hi there! How you doin'?

422
00:26:34,990 --> 00:26:40,390
<i>Hard time yearnin' where you go</i>

423
00:26:40,590 --> 00:26:45,990
<i>Times is harder than ever been before</i>

424
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:53,990
<i>And the people are driftin'</i>

425
00:26:54,190 --> 00:26:56,590
<i>From door to door</i>

426
00:26:56,890 --> 00:26:58,190
<i>Can't find no heaven</i>

427
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:01,590
<i>I don't care where they go</i>

428
00:27:11,790 --> 00:27:14,190
<i>Say you had money</i>

429
00:27:14,390 --> 00:27:16,790
<i>You better be sure</i>

430
00:27:16,990 --> 00:27:18,790
<i>These hard times will drive you</i>

431
00:27:18,990 --> 00:27:21,790
<i>From door to door</i>

432
00:27:33,090 --> 00:27:35,390
Let's bed down here for the night.

433
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:39,090
Yeah, it stinks in that old barn.

434
00:27:39,390 --> 00:27:40,690
Suits me.

435
00:27:40,990 --> 00:27:46,590
Pretty soon it'll be nothin' but
featherbeds and silk sheets.

436
00:27:49,590 --> 00:27:51,290
A million dollars.

437
00:27:51,590 --> 00:27:53,390
Million point two.

438
00:27:53,690 --> 00:27:58,190
- 500,000 each.
- 400, Delmar.

439
00:27:58,390 --> 00:28:04,790
Pete, what are you gonna do
with your share of the treasure ?

440
00:28:05,090 --> 00:28:07,490
Go out west somewhere.

441
00:28:07,690 --> 00:28:11,190
Open a fine restaurant.

442
00:28:11,290 --> 00:28:14,590
I'm gonna be the Maitre d'.

443
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:17,390
Greet all the swells.

444
00:28:17,590 --> 00:28:20,790
Go to work every day in a bow tie...

445
00:28:20,990 --> 00:28:22,990
tuxedo.

446
00:28:23,190 --> 00:28:26,590
And all the staff say "yes, sir" and...

447
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:28,090
"no, sir"...

448
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:31,590
and "in a jiffy, Pete"...

449
00:28:31,890 --> 00:28:35,790
And all my meals for free.

450
00:28:38,590 --> 00:28:40,390
What about you, Delmar,

451
00:28:40,590 --> 00:28:43,690
what are you gonna do with
your share of that dough?

452
00:28:43,990 --> 00:28:47,490
I'm gonna visit them foreclosin' son of a guns

453
00:28:47,690 --> 00:28:51,190
down at the Indianola Savings and Loan.

454
00:28:51,390 --> 00:28:57,190
Slap that money on the barrel head
and buy back the family farm.

455
00:28:57,390 --> 00:29:01,790
You ain't no kind of man if you ain't got land.

456
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:03,790
What about you, Everett?

457
00:29:04,090 --> 00:29:07,690
What you have in mind
when you stole it in the first place?

458
00:29:07,990 --> 00:29:13,990
Ahem. I... didn't have no plan.

459
00:29:14,190 --> 00:29:16,990
Well, that hardly sounds like you.

460
00:29:17,290 --> 00:29:20,390
All right, boys! It's the authorities!

461
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:23,090
Your situation is purt'nigh hopeless!

462
00:29:23,290 --> 00:29:25,590
Damn, they found our car.

463
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:28,790
We ain't got the time
and nary the inclination

464
00:29:29,090 --> 00:29:31,390
to shoo you boys any further.

465
00:29:31,690 --> 00:29:33,690
Damn, we got to skedaddle.

466
00:29:33,890 --> 00:29:37,690
I left my pomade in the car,
maybe I can creep up.

467
00:29:37,990 --> 00:29:42,090
Don't be a fool, Everett.
We got to R-U-N-N-O-F-T.

468
00:29:42,575 --> 00:29:44,190
Where's Tommy?

469
00:29:44,390 --> 00:29:49,390
Already lit out, scared out of his wits.

470
00:29:50,490 --> 00:29:53,290
Let's go!

471
00:29:53,490 --> 00:29:55,390
Well hell, it ain't square one.

472
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:59,490
Ain't no one gonna pick up three
filthy, unshaved hitchhikers.

473
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:03,590
And one of them a know-it-all
who can't keep his trap shut.

474
00:30:03,790 --> 00:30:07,890
Pete, the personal rancour reflected in that 
remark I don't intend to dignify with comment.

475
00:30:08,190 --> 00:30:12,190
But I would like to address your general
attitude of hopeless negativism.

